The club promises to increase its turnover by up to 30 percent from the signing of the contract.
The Spanish league leaders, clearly alarmed by the departure of one of the biggest stars, sought to thwart Neymar's departure, arguing that PSG would break the FFP rules.
"This is a clear case of 'financial doping' of both the club and the state's,' said the president of the Liga, Javier Teba, for the Spanish newspaper AS, referring to the ownership of the PSG club by the Qatari syndicate.
Arsenal manager Arsene Wenger, whose club is owned by the American sports magnate, shares La Liga's position on the club's funding.
