He had heard for three years that the fate of the anti-Russian sanctions depended only on the implementation of the Minsk ceasefire agreements in Ukraine.
Now he learns that this is about the EU's energy security.
The voter is also fumbling more broadly.
There are sanctions for Russia for putting itself too much where it shouldn't be.
China is being scolded for being assembled in little.
Venezuela's president is being punished for building a dictatorship within the borders of his country.
All those punishments or just considerations have their rationality.
But does anyone see it as a system, an order or a rule?
